 Introduction
This project aims to integrate social media and e-commerce functionalities using object-oriented programming techniques. It is designed to serve both end users and site administrators, providing powerful and secure tools for interacting with the platform.

 Features
 Social Media
- Following: Users can follow other profiles.
- Messaging: Private messaging between users.
- Interactions: Ability to like and comment on profiles and posts.

 E-commerce
- Browsing: Users can browse available products.
- Cart: Add products to the cart for future purchase.
- Secure Purchase: Secure process for purchasing visits and products.

 Administrative Backend
- Product Management: Tools to add, modify, and delete products.
- Visitor Reservations: Manage visitor bookings.
- Content Publishing: Publish and manage site content.
- Statistics: View website statistics.

 Full-Stack Development
The project is developed using a full-stack approach with the following technologies:
- HTML: Markup language for structuring web content.
- CSS: Stylesheet language for designing web pages.
- JavaScript: Scripting language for interactive web features.
- PHP: Server-side scripting language.
- MySQL: Relational database management system.

 Platform Security
- Backup Script: Implemented to regularly back up all data and save it in a secure file.
- Backup Automation: Configured to automatically send the backup file to a secure virtual machine for storage.
- Burp Suite Integration: Comprehensive security testing with Burp Suite.
  - Regular security assessments to identify vulnerabilities.
  - Tools to detect and remediate security issues such as SQL injection, cross-site scripting (XSS), and cross-site request forgery (CSRF).

 Source Code Management
- GitHub: Used for storing and distributing code.

